Package: BKBreed
Type: Package
Title: Colourful Biometrical Analysis for Plant Breeding and Genetics
Version: 0.3.1
Authors@R: person(given = "Praveen Kumar",
                   family = "B. K.",
                   role = c("aut", "cre"),
                   email = "bkpraveenars@gmail.com")
Description: A compact, colour-first toolkit for the analysis of plant breeding
    and genetics field experiments. It provides analysis of variance for the
    Randomised Block Design (RBD) and Factorial RBD, a check-anchored
    intra-block analysis for Augmented Alpha-Lattice designs, and the core
    biometrical-genetics workflow used in crop improvement: estimation of
    genetic variability (GCV, PCV, heritability, genetic advance), genotypic
    and phenotypic correlation, path-coefficient analysis, Line x Tester
    combining-ability analysis (GCA/SCA) and Griffing diallel analysis,
    Mahalanobis D-square
    genetic-divergence analysis with Tocher and hierarchical clustering, and
    genotype-by-environment stability analysis (Eberhart-Russell regression and
    Additive Main effects and Multiplicative Interaction, AMMI). Every analysis
    returns a tidy result object and a publication-ready 'ggplot2' figure using
    a bespoke high-contrast colour system. Designed to be small, accurate and
    visually distinct from existing agricultural-statistics packages.
